      "createdAt": "2025-01-19T16:47:15.205Z",
      "author": "skmdc (SK)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Allow setting default values for subitems. There are several requests for the same since 2021 but there has been no update so resurfacing the feature request again.</p>\n<aside class=\"quote quote-modified\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/k/f04885/48.png\" class=\"avatar\" />\n    <a href=\"/#/t/37983\">Set default values for subitems</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/7\"><span style=\"--category-badge-color:#ffcc00;--category-badge-text-color:#FFFFFF\" class=\"badge-category \"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    I would like to set sub-item default values like I can with regular items. This would help set the default status. \n <a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/2X/2/2045906014bece0c87c2c11ec895925d4faf5e97.jpeg\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">[image]</a>\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n<aside class=\"quote\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/d/7993a0/48.png\" class=\"avatar\" />\n    <a href=\"/#/t/26535\">Default Value for sub items</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/platform-discussions/6\"><span style=\"--category-badge-color:#00ca72;--category-badge-text-color:#FFFFFF\" class=\"badge-category \"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Platform discussions</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Can I set default value for sub items? I need new sub items to default to red color. Basically using sub items as a check list\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n<aside class=\"quote\">\n  <div class=\"title\">\n    <div class=\"quote-controls\"></div>\n    <img alt=\"\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" src=\"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/k/a9adbd/48.png\" class=\"avatar\" />\n    <a href=\"/#/t/44372\">Subitem default values</a> <a class=\"badge-category__wrapper \" href=\"/c/feature-requests/7\"><span style=\"--category-badge-color:#ffcc00;--category-badge-text-color:#FFFFFF\" class=\"badge-category \"><span class=\"badge-category__name\">Feature requests</span></span></a>\n  </div>\n  <blockquote>\n    Hi, item default values already available, please consider apply that default ability for subitems too.\n  </blockquote>\n</aside>\n"
    },
    {
      "id": 218118,
      "postNumber": 2,
      "createdAt": "2025-01-20T16:43:55.953Z",
      "author": "Do_Zoo (Nate)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hey <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/skmdc\">@skmdc</a> , I’d love to work with you on this problem! I’m a new developer and am looking for a good first project to get started on. Is there a specific way you’re thinking this should look like in the UI? feel free to DM me as well <img src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/apple/slight_smile.png?v=12\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" /></p>"
    },
    {
      "id": 218526,
      "postNumber": 3,
      "createdAt": "2025-01-22T22:34:45.365Z",
      "author": "skmdc (SK)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>I would suggest just adding another option in the same menu just like there is today for the parent items using the Options menu (… at the top right corner of the board)</p>\n<p></p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/9/b/9b47e1d1503760259e8398abf1d72727f9249cab.png\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/9/b/9b47e1d1503760259e8398abf1d72727f9249cab_2_473x500.png\" alt=\"image\" width=\"473\" height=\"500\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">image</span><span class=\"informations\">1130×1194 80.3 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>The option could be called - Default subitem values</p>"
    },
    {
      "id": 218645,
      "postNumber": 4,
      "createdAt": "2025-01-23T13:22:24.031Z",
      "author": "Fantasy-Media-Team (Fantasy Media Team)",
      "cookedHtml": "<p>Hey <a class=\"mention\" href=\"/u/skmdc\">@skmdc</a></p>\n<p>We developed an <a href=\"https://monday.com/marketplace/10000287\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">app</a> that solves this exact use case in 3 different ways.</p>\n<p>First, setting default values based on the items name see below (this is an example, you can use pretty much any column) -<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/4/1/414dfc816a8141f6d0a740b5349532e32c326d2b.png\" title=\"Screenshot 2024-01-10 at 10.51.08\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/4/1/414dfc816a8141f6d0a740b5349532e32c326d2b_2_690x127.png\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-10 at 10.51.08\" width=\"690\" height=\"127\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot 2024-01-10 at 10.51.08</span><span class=\"informations\">2126×392 37.1 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>Second, inheriting the date from the parent item -<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/c/4/c4eed93e5a9478543a6917229f46b9848c7701d5.png\" title=\"Screenshot 2024-01-10 at 10.52.02\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/c/4/c4eed93e5a9478543a6917229f46b9848c7701d5_2_690x140.png\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-10 at 10.52.02\" width=\"690\" height=\"140\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot 2024-01-10 at 10.52.02</span><span class=\"informations\">2026×412 40.7 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>Third, just a default value based on creation date -<br />\n</p><div class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"><a class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/original/3X/1/3/132082e783bd4cdc6b5293ee9eaf33521686e2ac.png\" title=\"Screenshot 2024-01-10 at 10.51.47\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"><img src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/monday/optimized/3X/1/3/132082e783bd4cdc6b5293ee9eaf33521686e2ac_2_690x130.png\" alt=\"Screenshot 2024-01-10 at 10.51.47\" width=\"690\" height=\"130\" /><div class=\"meta\"><span class=\"filename\">Screenshot 2024-01-10 at 10.51.47</span><span class=\"informations\">2014×382 28.3 KB</span></div></a></div><p></p>\n<p>You can find it in the <a href=\"http://monday.com\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">monday.com</a> marketplace in the platform or here - <a href=\"https://monday.com/marketplace/10000287\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Subitem Automations - monday.com Marketplace</a></p>\n<p>Hope that helps!</p>"
    }
